he object's original world.","why_it_matters":"It matters because this textile keeps its intended work visible: how it was used, displayed, valued, or carried across time.","latitude":-9.19,"longitude":-75.0152,"week_key":"full-archive-2026-W27"},{"id":"artic-panel-85467","title":"Panel","maker":"Chim\u00fa","culture":"Peru","country":null,"region":null,"date_display":"1250-1470","category":"textile","image_url":"https://www.artic.edu/iiif/2/570d6bdc-a93c-4d68-c103-398691d69947/full/843,/0/default.jpg","source_name":"Art Institute of Chicago","source_url":"https://www.artic.edu/artworks/85467","license":"Public domain / Art Institute of Chicago","hook":"A textile from Peru, 1250-1470, with animal and frog bringing its subject into focus.","story":"Panel is a textile by Chim\u00fa, from Peru, dated 1250-1470, made with cotton and camelid wool, slit tapestry weave with eccentric wefts. It was made through slow handwork, where use, display, pattern, and memory could share the same surface. The use of animal and frog anchors the composition and gives the viewer a direct point of entry into its subject.","why_it_matters":"It matters because it treats thread, pattern, and domestic labor as serious cultural evidence.","latitude":-9.19,"longitude":-75.0152,"week_key":"full-archive-2026-W27"},{"id":"artic-panel-100741","title":"Panel","maker":"Philippe de La Salle","culture":"France","country":null,"region":null,"date_display":"c. 1775","category":"textile","image_url":"https://www.artic.edu/iiif/2/2bfae1e6-8acc-693e-25c7-1d4d681f9ce7/full/843,/0/default.jpg","source_name":"Art Institute of Chicago","source_url":"https://www.artic.edu/artworks/100741","license":"Public domain / Art Institute of Chicago","hook":"A textile from France, c. 1775, with animal, bird, and flower bringing its subject into focus.","story":"Panel is a textile by Philippe de La Salle, from France, dated c. 1775, made with silk and linen, satin weave with brocading wefts. It was made through slow handwo