d States, 1870-1900, with owl bringing its subject into focus.","story":"Owl and Pussycat Covered Tray is a ceramic vessel by Artist unknown, from United States, dated 1870-1900, made with glass. It was made to hold, pour, serve, or present something, so its decoration had to live with use. The use of owl anchors the composition and gives the viewer a direct point of entry into its subject. Seen in its original material and scale, the subject also shows how closely image, surface, and making were connected.","why_it_matters":"It matters because it lets everyday or ritual use carry imagery, with owl turning a container into a cultural record.","latitude":37.0902,"longitude":-95.7129,"week_key":"full-archive-2026-W27"},{"id":"artic-oinochoe-pitcher-246","title":"Oinochoe (Pitcher)","maker":"Mattinata Painter","culture":"Greece","country":null,"region":null,"date_display":"end of 4th century BCE","category":"pottery","image_url":"https://www.artic.edu/iiif/2/44abac03-4d36-aac6-f44e-ffe1d57dfb03/full/843,/0/default.jpg","source_name":"Art Institute of Chicago","source_url":"https://www.artic.edu/artworks/246","license":"Public domain / Art Institute of Chicago","hook":"A ceramic vessel from Greece, end of 4th century BCE made vivid by terracotta, red-figure.","story":"Oinochoe (Pitcher) is a ceramic vessel by Mattinata Painter, from Greece, dated end of 4th century BCE, made with terracotta, red-figure. It was made to hold, pour, serve, or present something, so its decoration had to live with use. The terracotta, red-figure is part of the meaning because material decides weight, shine, durability, and how close a viewer wants to look.","why_it_matters":"It matters because it lets practical use and visual meaning occupy the same handled form. It keeps the object's purpose legible instead of leaving only a label.","latitude":39.0742,"longitude":21.8243,"week_key":"full-archive-2026-W27"},{"id":"artic-miniature-mountain-with-shoulao-god-of-longevity-the-eight-daois-142421","title":"Miniature Mountain with Shoulao (God of Longevity), the Eight Daoist Immortals, Scholars on Horseback, Monkey with Peach, and Deer with Mushroom of Immortality","maker":"China","culture":"China","country":null,"region":null,"date_display":"Ming dynasty (1368\u20131644), 16th century","category":"sculpture","image_url":"https://www.artic.edu/iiif/2/ebb25bd0-65e3-eca5-077b-3ecbaf0aa967/full/843,/0/default.jpg","source_name":"Art Institute of Chicago","source_url":"https://www.artic.edu/artworks/142421","license":"Public domain / Art Institute of Chicago","hook":"A sculpture from China, Ming dynasty, 16th century, with deer and monkey bringing its subject into focus.","story":"Miniature Mountain with Shoulao (God of Longevity), the Eight Daoist Immortals, Scholars on Horseback, Monkey with Peach, and Deer with Mushroom of Immortality is a sculpture by China, from China, dated Ming dynasty, 16th century, made with ivory. It was made to give a body, symbol, or story physical presence in space. The use of deer and monkey anchors the composition and gives the viewer a direct point of entry into its subject.","why_it_matters":"It matters because it gives cultural meaning a body, weight, and physical presence. It keeps the object's purpose legible instead of leaving only a label.","latitude":35.8617,"longitude":104.1954,"week_key":"full-archive-2026-W27"}]$_hc$::jsonb as doc
